[TITLE]
Rule priority tie-breaking — two conflicting rules at different priorities

[JUNCTIONS]
J1    100    100
J2    100    50

[RESERVOIRS]
R1    0

[TANKS]
T1    150    5    0    10    20    0

[PIPES]
P1    J1    J2    500     12    100    0    Open
P2    J2    T1    500     12    100    0    Open

[PUMPS]
PMP1    R1    J1    HEAD C1

[CURVES]
C1    0    300
C1    500    200

[RULES]
; Low-priority rule wants pump ON when tank below 4
RULE 1
IF NODE T1 LEVEL BELOW 4.0
THEN LINK PMP1 STATUS IS OPEN
PRIORITY 1

; High-priority rule wants pump OFF when tank below 2
; (e.g. maintenance override — the higher priority wins)
RULE 2
IF NODE T1 LEVEL BELOW 2.0
THEN LINK PMP1 STATUS IS CLOSED
PRIORITY 3

; Turn pump off once tank fills above 7
RULE 3
IF NODE T1 LEVEL ABOVE 7.0
THEN LINK PMP1 STATUS IS CLOSED
PRIORITY 2

[OPTIONS]
Units    GPM
Headloss    H-W

[TIMES]
Duration    24:00
Hydraulic Timestep    1:00
Report Timestep    1:00

[END]
